3 Section 6. Section 75-10-1304, MCA, is amended to read:
4 "75-10-1304. Contractor certification -- department authority. (1) The department is authorized to
5 shall establish by rule minimum standards for the training and certification of contractors and their employees
6 who are to perform the assessment or remediation of inhabitable property or volunteer property contaminated
7 by methamphetamine or fentanyl residues or other dangerous drug residues.
8 (2) The department may shall may train and test or may shall may approve courses to train and
9 test contractors and their employees in the proper methods of assessing, remediating, and testing inhabitable
10 property or volunteer property contaminated by methamphetamine residues or other dangerous drug fentanyl
11 residues. If the department conducts the training and testing of contractors and their employees, it may adopt
12 rules to provide for the assessment of reasonable fees to cover the state's costs of providing the training and
13 testing.
14 (3) The department shall establish by rule procedures for the certification of contractors and their
15 employees, including procedures for the decertification of contractors and their employees for cause. The rules
16 may provide for the assessment of reasonable fees to cover the cost of the contractor certification program.
17 (4) Any contractor and the contractor's employees certified to perform the remediation of
18 inhabitable property in any other state are approved for certification in Montana unless the department
19 determines that the certification process in the other state is not substantially similar to the minimum
20 certification standards established by the department must complete refresher training by the department or a
21 department-approved training provider to qualify for certification in Montana.
22 (5) The department shall maintain a list of certified contractors and shall make the list available to
23 local health officials, law enforcement officials, and the public."
24
